# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- Solve using calculating Slopes

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- We will select point and for every selected point we will calculate the slope with respect to another point and store into the map.
- Then, find the max number of points having the same slope with respect to that selected point :-means which slope have maximum point

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n^2)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

<!-- - Space complexity: -->
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
