solutions.content:
# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Only use integer computations. I reguard this question as a Diophantine problem.

Since all points are with integer coefficients, it is very crucial how to parametize such linear equations
$$
ax+by=c
$$
where $a, b, c \in Z$ with $\gcd( a, b, c)=1\ &  \ c>0$. 
If the constraint is changed, a linear equation has the following form:
$$
y=mx+c
$$
where $m\in R\cup\{\infty\}, c\in R$. note that when $m=\infty$, it means $x=d$ for some $d\in R$. Use this approach, there is no need for computation for gcds but using float computation.
# Approach 1
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
![binary_line0.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/afecb0bb-e83d-41af-91e6-c8cf4cbefc64_1688826474.8209305.png)
Some modififications should be made! 2 different tuples $(a, b, c)$ and $(a', b', c')$ represent the same line and are similar $\iff$
$$ \exists d\in Z \ & \ d\not= 0 : (a, b, c)=(da', db', dc')
$$
One way to find the representative for all similar tuples is to choose $(a, b, c)$ such tat $\gcd(a, b,c)=1$ with the following conditions: (It should be noticed that it may happen that c=0 what is not to ignore! )
```
int d = gcd(a, b); //c is an integer linear combination of a & b therefore d|c
a /= d, b /= d, c /= d;
if (c < 0) {
      a = -a, b = -b, c = -c;
}
else if (c==0){ // This can occur!
    if (b<0 || (a<0 && b==0)) a=-a, b=-b;
}
```

