# Intuition
Simple Geometry: (y2-y1)/(x2-x1)= slope of line passing two points.

# Approach
```
For every point we will calculate the slope of line which 
passes through other points one by one and add the slope in the 
map to keep count of the max points of same slope.
here slope will be key, count of slope points will be value.
Edge Case: if x2-x1 is 0 then it doesn't matter what are the
values of y2 and y1 as slope will be INFINITY because we are
dividing by zero. 
At last return the mx+1 as we have to include the point for which
we are calculating the slope counts.
Dry run once You Will Understand Clearly.
```


