solutions.content:
> What are points `lie on the same straight line` like?
> 
>The ratio of the "vertical change" to the "horizontal change" between (any) two distinct points on a line is identical, which is called **slope**. 

> For each point i, itself and another point j can identify a line, resulting in a slope. 
> We map a slope to its frequency. Finally, frequency + 1 is the number of points on the line with the `slope`.
> 
> As for the slope, we need to transfer it to a fraction in lowest terms.

> Since `from point i to j`, and `from point j to i` is the same line. We can start j from i + 1.

> There may be points overlapping with i. We maintain `overlap` and add it to total points at last.
```
    public int maxPoints(int[][] points) {
        if (points.length == 0) {
            return 0;
        }

        // Maximum points among slopes
        int max = 0;
        // Map slope to its frequency
        Map<String, Integer> kToFreq;

        for (int i = 0; i < points.length; i++) { // For each point i
            kToFreq = new HashMap<>(); 
            int overlap = 0; // The number of points overlap with i

            for (int j = i + 1; j < points.length; j++) { // For each point j

                int yDiff = points[j][1] - points[i][1];
                int xDiff = points[j][0] - points[i][0];

                if (xDiff == 0 && yDiff == 0) { // Point j overlaps point i
                    overlap++;
                } else if (xDiff == 0) { // Point j and i are parallel
                    kToFreq.put("Max", kToFreq.getOrDefault("Max", 0) + 1);
                } else {
                    int sign = 
                        ((xDiff > 0 && yDiff > 0) || (xDiff < 0 && yDiff < 0)) ? 1 : -1;
                    xDiff = Math.abs(xDiff);
                    yDiff = Math.abs(yDiff);
                    int gcd = getGCD(xDiff, yDiff);
                    String k = sign + " " + xDiff / gcd  + "/" + yDiff / gcd;
                    kToFreq.put(k, kToFreq.getOrDefault(k, 0) + 1);
                }
            }

            // Update max with max value in current map
            int curMax = 0;
            for (int freq : kToFreq.values()) {
                curMax = Math.max(curMax, freq);
            }
            max = Math.max(curMax + overlap + 1, max);
        }

        return max;
    }

    private int getGCD(int a, int b) {
        if (b == 0) {
            return a;
        }
        return getGCD(b, a % b);
    }
